<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Chicken Kabsa Recipe</title>
</head>
<body>

    <!-- صورة الكبسة في وسط الصفحة -->
    <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/5e/Kabsa_Chicken.jpg" 
         alt="Kabsa Dish" width="400" 
         style="display:block; margin-left:auto; margin-right:auto;">

    <h1 style="text-align:center;">Chicken Kabsa</h1>

    <p style="text-align:center; max-width:600px; margin:auto;">
        Chicken Kabsa is a popular rice dish made with chicken, rice, tomatoes,
        onions, and warm spices. It is full of flavour and is often served as a
        main meal for lunch or dinner.
    </p>

    <h2>Ingredients</h2>

    <ul>
        <li>2 cups basmati rice</li>
        <li>4 pieces of chicken</li>
        <li>1 large onion, chopped</li>
        <li>2 tomatoes, chopped</li>
        <li>2 cloves of garlic, crushed</li>
        <li>2 tablespoons cooking oil</li>
        <li>1 teaspoon salt</li>
        <li>1 teaspoon black pepper</li>
        <li>1 teaspoon mixed spices</li>
        <li>3 cups water or chicken stock</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Method</h2>

    <ol>
        <li>Wash the basmati rice and soak it in water for about 20 minutes.</li>
        <li>Heat the cooking oil in a large pot.</li>
        <li>Add the chopped onion and cook until it becomes soft.</li>
        <li>Add the garlic, tomatoes, salt, pepper, and mixed spices.</li>
        <li>Add the chicken pieces and cook them for a few minutes.</li>
        <li>Pour in the water or chicken stock and let the chicken cook.</li>
        <li>Add the rice to the pot and stir gently.</li>
        <li>Cover the pot and cook on low heat until the rice is soft.</li>
        <li>Serve the chicken kabsa hot on a large plate.</li>
    </ol>

</body>
</html>